China and India will hold the 15th round of corps commander-level talks on March 11, China's Foreign Ministry spokesperson Zhao Lijian announced on Wednesday. The 14th round of the China-India Corps Commander Level Meeting was held at the Moldo-Chushul border meeting point on the Chinese side on January 12. During the meeting, the two sides had a frank and in-depth exchange of views for the resolution of relevant issues along the Line of Actual Control (LAC) in the Western Sector of China-India border areas. It is hoped that the two sides can continue to move forward on the basis of previous talks, further expand consensus, narrow differences and strive to reach a mutually acceptable solution, Zhao said. (Cover: File photo of China's Foreign Ministry spokesperson Zhao Lijian. /China's Foreign Ministry )